How to prepare earthworms so they don't taste like dirt:
1) Put earthworms in a bowl/pot of fresh water. Leave them there until their intestines are empty. This can take up to a few hours. They will not drown immediately, but they will slowly drown over time.
2) Once no more poop comes out, take them out of the water, put a pot with a bit of clean water on the fire and put the worms in the clean pot to boil. You don't need a lot of water, just make sure they're just completely submerged.
3) Once the worms are boiled, cut them up and rinse them again to get rid of the final bits of dirt and poop.
4) Now you can process them like most meats. Grind the pieces to make minced meat for meatballs or burgers, fry the pieces with some chopped onions and/or other herbs/spices/vegetables, etc.

Alternatively, you can slowly bake them on a tray until they're completely dry, then grind them into powder with your mortar and pestle. This makes a kind of protein powder that you can use to thicken soup, add to flour or whatever you want. It's a way to get the protein without the earthworm flavour.
